3. ORIGINAL WEBSITE ASSETS — NOT LICENSED
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Screenshots, descriptions, and any analysis of third-party websites
(such as Apple, Linear, Stripe, etc.) are intended solely as
educational and design-research references. The original brand
assets, typography, copy, and visual identity remain the property
of their respective owners.

OpenDesign extracts and describes design *principles* (color tokens,
typography categories, layout rhythm) — it does NOT redistribute
brand assets. If you are a rights holder and wish a reference
removed, open an issue.


4. AI-GENERATED CONTENT — CC BY 4.0
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Design specifications generated by AI vision models (such as those
in sites-specs.json) are released under CC BY 4.0 as part of the
curated data.
